HEADWORD: Circumscissile
<hw>Cir`cum*scis"sile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>circum-</ets> + <ets>scissle</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Dehiscing or opening by a transverse fissure extending around (a
capsule or pod). See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Pyxidium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumscribable</ent>⟦br⟧
